HEADWORD: Reporter
<hw>Re*port"er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
reports.</def> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An
officer or person who makes authorized statements of law proceedings and
decisions, or of legislative debates.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One who
reports speeches, the proceedings of public meetings, news, etc., for
the newspapers.</def><-- ##?? add other media -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of our tales judge and <qex>reportour</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reportingly</ent>⟦br⟧
